The article is a transcript of a speech given by Vice President Kamala Harris at the West Haven Child Development Center in West Haven, Connecticut. In the speech, Harris emphasizes the importance of supporting children and investing in their futures. She praises Congresswoman Rosa DeLauro for her work and discusses the significance of the American Rescue Plan in lifting children out of poverty. Harris also highlights the need for affordable childcare, the value of educators, and the opportunity to address racial disparities and other systemic issues. She encourages optimism and collaboration in creating a better future for children.